        ". If the excess hoof is not trimmed, the bones will become misaligned, which would place stress on the legs of the animal. Evans, J. Warren, et al. The Horse. Second edition, New York: Freeman, 1990, , pp. 742–747.     Shoes are then measured to the foot and bent to the correct shape using a hammer, anvil, forge, and other modifications, such as taps for ": null
